<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="115" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,912,1301,1328]" box="[151,912,1301,1328]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,912,1301,1328]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="14" pageNumber="115" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,912,1301,1328]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">
Genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Chen, Nieser" authorityName="Chen, Nieser" box="[238,554,1301,1328]" class="Insecta" family="Macroveliidae" genus="Pleciogonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[238,386,1301,1327]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">Pleciogonus</emphasis>
Chen, Nieser
</taxonomicName>
, &amp; Wattanachaiyingcharoen
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,1372,1541]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">
This monotypic genus is represented by 
<taxonomicName authority="Chen, Nieser" authorityName="Chen, Nieser" box="[612,1023,1372,1397]" class="Insecta" family="Macroveliidae" genus="Pleciogonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wongsirii">
<emphasis box="[612,865,1373,1397]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">Pleciogonus wongsirii</emphasis>
Chen, Nieser
</taxonomicName>
, &amp; Wattanachaiyingcharoen and has been recorded only from 
<collectingCountry box="[439,539,1408,1433]" name="Thailand" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">Thailand</collectingCountry>
(Chen et al. 
<number box="[688,749,1409,1433]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115" value="2002.0">2002</number>
). This genus is found in montane streams (Chen et al. 
<number box="[1371,1429,1409,1433]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115" value="2002.0">2002</number>
) and is closely related to 
<emphasis box="[435,574,1445,1469]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">Andersenius</emphasis>
Zettel &amp; Chen and 
<emphasis box="[808,939,1445,1469]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">Pleciobates</emphasis>
Esaki; however, 
<taxonomicName box="[1140,1277,1445,1468]" class="Insecta" family="Macroveliidae" genus="Pleciogonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wongsirii">
<emphasis box="[1140,1154,1445,1468]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1171,1277,1445,1468]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">wongsirii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can easily be separated from the other genera based on color pattern (
<bibRefCitation author="Chen" box="[776,1005,1480,1505]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115" refString="Chen, P. - P. &amp; Zettel, H. (1998) Key to genera and subgenera of Gerridae (Gerromorpha) of Thailand and adjacent countries, with a check-list of species known from Thailand. Amemboa, 2, 24 - 41." type="journal article" year="1998">
Chen &amp; Zettel 
<number box="[945,1005,1481,1505]" pageId="14" pageNumber="115" value="1998.0">1998</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). More specifically, 
<taxonomicName box="[1234,1372,1481,1505]" class="Insecta" family="Macroveliidae" genus="Pleciogonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1234,1372,1481,1505]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">Pleciogonus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a yellow mesopleuron whereas 
<emphasis box="[484,622,1517,1541]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">Andersenius</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[677,808,1517,1541]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="115">Pleciobates</emphasis>
have dark mesopleura.
</paragraph>
